In ventral view, the incisive foramen (palatine fissure) is short and located at the level of the anterior aspect of the upper canine. A tiny foramen is present along the midline suture at the junction of the premaxillary and maxillary (foramen palatine medialis of 
Story, 1951
), as is commonly seen in arctoids. The maxillary–palatine suture is mostly fused and difficult to recognize. The palatine foramen is somewhat behind the level of the P4 protocone. The posterior border of the palatine bone is anterior to the posterior border of the M2 and is distinctly indented by a semicircular notch on either side of the midline suture.
